00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:03,411
All right.

527
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:07,919
Okay, so, your dad's a preacher.
He knows a lot of things,

528
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:11,283
but he didn't know
that Jesus has a horse.

529
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:13,165
Didn't know that.

530
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,319
It's beautiful.

531
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,799
Yeah? What color is it?

532
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:19,599
It's all the colors.

533
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,719
All the colors of the
rainbow are in heaven,

534
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:26,527
except they're all more.

535
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:27,959
More what?

536
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,162
Just more and brighter.

537
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:33,599
How do you know about this horse?

538
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:35,609
Because I saw him in heaven.

539
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,559
You were in heaven?

540
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:40,799
Dad, can we talk
about this tomorrow

541
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:43,359
because I'm getting really sleepy.

542
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,766
Okay.

543
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:48,285
Dad, can I sleep in
your room tonight?

544
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:52,319
No. No, we're going to
go ahead and sleep here.

545
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:54,522
It's late, guys. Come on.

546
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:59,279
Open the door!

547
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,606
Sorry.

548
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,246
Hmm.

549
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:07,131
Are you asleep?

550
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,441
Colton just told me
he went to heaven.

551
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:14,649
What? When?

552
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,611
Just now.

553
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:20,329
No, when did he go to heaven?

554
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:25,688
He said that during his
operation, he left his body,

555
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:30,446
and he looked back on the
operating table and saw himself.

556
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:35,283
He has a very
beautiful imagination.

557
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:44,599
I'll do it, too.
I'll have the same thing.

558
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:47,719
Hi, how are you, Rosa? Can we
get, uh... What do you think?

559
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:48,839
Milkshake.

560
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:50,644
Two milkshakes, please.

561
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,923
- How is everything?
- Okay, great.

562
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:56,650
So, Colton,

563
00:36:57,520 --> 00:37:00,399
I want to ask you about when
the angels sang to you.

564
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,761
Sure.

565
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:51,001
I was alone, but I wasn't scared.

566
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:55,324
I was at the church.

567
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:57,519
The door was closed.

568
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,529
I opened it.

569
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:16,239
And I saw something wonderful.

570
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:30,202
♪ Hallelujah

571
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:33,762
♪ Hallelujah ♪

572
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:59,362
I saw angels and they
were singing to me.

573
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:13,251
Can we sing "We Will Rock You"?

574
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:38,203
Colton, do you know who I am?

575
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:41,325
You're not afraid?

576
00:39:42,120 --> 00:39:44,687
Nobody here wants to hurt me.

577
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,759
That's right, Colton.

578
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:48,928
And nobody here ever will.

579
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:52,205
There are some people here
who want to meet you.

580
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:14,007
So, what did they sing?

581
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:18,331
I asked them to sing "We Will
Rock You", but they wouldn't.

582
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,887
And they laughed just like that.

583
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:28,851
Mmm, milkshake.

584
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,559
Moreland University,
Department of Psychology,

585
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,759
Chairman's office.

586
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:34,399
May I speak with
Dr. Slater, please?

587
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,879
Are you calling for an appointment?

588
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:39,448
Yeah. Is there any chance
she could see me today?

589
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:50,239
- Dr. Slater?
- Yes.

590
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:53,159
Hi. I'm Todd Burpo.

591
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,681
Oh, yes, please come in.

592
00:40:57,600 --> 00:41:00,246
Thanks for, uh,
seeing me on short notice.

593
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:03,959
Um, "Burpo." Are you a
minister over in Imperial?

594
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:06,319
Yeah. Yes. How'd you know that?

595
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:09,729
Uh, my late husband was religious.
Please, sit.

596
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:13,559
Uh, he had heard about a speaker
named Burpo who was very interesting

597
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:16,206
and he kept badgering me
to come hear you.

598
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:17,766
You're not?

599
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,119
Not what?

600
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:20,446
Religious.

601
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:23,486
No. Is that a problem?

602
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:24,767
No.

603
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,959
No, you might offer me
a harder opinion,

604
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:31,448
help me find a more rational
understanding for something.

605
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:36,759
I have a son who's, uh,
extremely smart.

606
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:38,610
And he's sensitive.

607
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:43,127
And?

608
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,245
He went to heaven.

609
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,524
And then he came back.

610
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:54,159
Your son had
a near-death experience?

611
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,759
No, he didn't die.

612
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:58,611
We checked his surgical reports.

613
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:03,166
His heart never stopped, his
brain activity never flatlined.

614
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:05,159
So, why do you say
he went to heaven?

615
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:07,169
Because he says he did.

616
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:09,919
At the point near death,

617
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:11,239
the body releases hormones

618
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:14,330
that can induce a state
of peace, even bliss.

619
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,399
Our brains fill in the blanks.

620
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:20,479
Christians see Jesus, Jews see
Moses, Muslims see Muhammad.

621
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:22,319
Yeah, I read your article,

622
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:25,799
but my son saw things
that I can't really explain.

623
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:29,482
He saw me praying. He saw me

624
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:31,039
shouting at God.

625
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:33,879
He saw his mother in another
wing calling friends,

626
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:37,402
asking them to pray for us. All
the while, he was in surgery.

627
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:40,527
- Reverend Burpo...
- Todd.

628
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:42,286
Todd.

629
00:42:43,720 --> 00:42:46,959
Is it unusual for your wife to
call friends in a time of crisis?

630
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:49,959
No. No, it's not.

631
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,119
And is it unusual for you to pray?

632
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:53,679
Or become passionate when you do?

633
00:42:53,680 --> 00:42:57,248
No. No. Of course not.
But I know my son.

634
00:42:57,960 --> 00:42:59,679
And when he talks about heaven,

635
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:03,039
it doesn't sound like
something he's making up.

636
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,759
He's very specific. He's four.

637
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:06,079
And he's extremely smart.

638
00:43:06,080 --> 00:43:09,250
Yes. Both of my kids are.

639
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:10,846
Reverend...

640
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:16,119
Todd, I don't mean to
discount whatever magic it is

641
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:17,839
you derive from all of this,

642
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:20,279
but there are many explanations,

643
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:22,482
even for extrasensory knowledge.

644
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:28,519
Is it really easier
to believe in that

645
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:30,559
or clairvoyance

646
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:34,039
or telepathy than it is
life after the physical?

647
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:35,730
Believe in miracles?

648
00:43:36,200 --> 00:43:39,085
I've found such concepts
to be a bit circular.

649
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:42,361
Even before I watched
my husband die.

650
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:47,919
Let me ask you, did you
come here today because

651
00:43:47,920 --> 00:43:50,199
you were wondering about my faith?

652
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:52,607
Or were you wondering
about your own?

653
00:43:55,120 --> 00:43:56,970
Thanks for your time.

654
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:00,971
You're welcome.

655
00:44:08,920 --> 00:44:11,599
What if you have
an encounter so far

656
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:16,169
beyond your own
experience that it's

657
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:20,000
irrational?

658
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:22,680
What then?

659
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:47,439
This looks like trouble here.

660
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:49,879
- Todd, we're so happy about Colton.
- Thank you.

661
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:53,527
Thanks. Thank you very much.
See you later. Good.

662
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:01,599
There he is.

663
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,719
- How are you doing, buddy?
- Good. How are you?

664
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,239
How's that Colton doing today?

665
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,568
Is he back to torturing his sister?

666
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:10,768
Yes.

667
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:14,359
I need some advice, smart advice.

668
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:17,079
Well, I am not smart, so you
came to the right guy.

669
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:18,199
I know that.

670
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:21,839
Nothing but clumsy, inaccurate
advice available here.

671
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:24,088
I've been expecting to
see you a little sooner.

672
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:25,679
What do you mean?

673
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:27,530
Well, I'm your banker.

674
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:30,119
I didn't come here for a loan.

675
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:33,479
Not the bank's money, just
from a friend to a friend.

676
00:45:33,480 --> 00:45:36,319
Let me help you out, okay?
Nobody would have to know.

677
00:45:36,320 --> 00:45:37,681
I'd know.

678
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,599
I never wanted to be the guy who
stands up there in the pulpit

679
00:45:40,600 --> 00:45:43,399
asking people to give to charity
when all he does is take it.

680
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:47,959
It's not charity. It's a loan
from a friend to a friend.

681
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:50,999
I know you need the help.
It's what real people do.

682
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:52,440
I don't.

683
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:56,479
Well, then you didn't come
here for smart advice.

684
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:59,039
I don't think the church has
kept your salary in line with

685
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:00,559
the new members
that you've brought in.

686
00:46:00,560 --> 00:46:02,439
I think you deserve a raise.

687
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:05,119
Let me talk to the board,
see what I can do.

688
00:46:05,120 --> 00:46:07,639
I didn't come here
for a raise, either.

689
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:10,719
All right. Good.

690
00:46:10,720 --> 00:46:12,684
I didn't want to ask them.

691
00:46:12,960 --> 00:46:15,288
What can I do for you?

692
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:17,286
It's Colton.

693
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,286
He's been talking about this, uh...

694
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:25,399
We ask these kids
to believe this stuff

695
00:46:25,400 --> 00:46:28,279
and I don't even know
if I believe it myself, Jay.

696
00:46:28,280 --> 00:46:29,839
What?

697
00:46:37,720 --> 00:46:39,479
Colton is what I'm trying
to tell you about.

698
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:42,079
He's been saying things
I don't understand.

699
00:46:42,080 --> 00:46:44,799
He's talking about these
conversations in heaven.

700
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,439
I used to go out
with a flight attendant

701
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:50,008
whose son had extensive conversations
with Barney the dinosaur.

702
00:46:50,520 --> 00:46:53,279
- Do you know how irritating Barney is?
- Yeah.

703
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:55,799
- He's purple.
- Exactly, exactly.

704
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:58,844
The Bible tells us to
believe his children.

705
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:02,359
What my child's telling me will
get me laughed out of this town.

706
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:04,999
That's what I'm saying.
I don't know what to preach.

707
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:06,519
I don't have anything to say.

708
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:09,610
Just speak from the heart,
Todd, like you always do.

709
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:17,239
What about fear do we
struggle with? Is it confusion?

710
00:47:17,240 --> 00:47:19,841
Is it doubt? Is it questions?

711
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:21,645
I got questions.

712
00:47:22,600 --> 00:47:25,280
We all do. Maybe we
ought to just...

713
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:29,039
Maybe we ought to try that today.
Just see if, uh...

714
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:31,083
Do you want to try questions?

715
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:40,489
- Hey, Todd.
- Yeah?

716
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:42,759
My family and I
prayed for you a lot.

717
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:44,849
Thank you. Thank you, Michael.

718
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:47,527
Uh, we're just wondering,
how bad was it?

719
00:47:47,760 --> 00:47:49,999
"How bad?" It was awful.

720
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:53,559
I mean, a lot of us heard that
Colton died during the operation

721
00:47:53,560 --> 00:47:56,411
and prayers
brought him back to life.

722
00:47:57,400 --> 00:48:00,922
Uh, no, he didn't die
on the operating table.

723
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:03,119
He, you know, came mighty close,

724
00:48:03,120 --> 00:48:06,210
but I think it was the doctors,

725
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:09,519
through God and all of your
prayers, that kept him alive

726
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:12,166
and so thank you all for that.

727
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:14,199
So, how did you handle it?

728
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,639
Not well.

729
00:48:15,640 --> 00:48:20,679
But the important thing is that the
Burpos faced a significant challenge

730
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:23,159
and they came through it. Amen.

731
00:48:23,160 --> 00:48:24,805
Amen.

732
00:48:27,160 --> 00:48:28,439
That's the thing, though.

733
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:32,201
Thank you for that, Jay, but I don't
know that I did come through.

734
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:36,399
Colton's experience
makes me wonder.

735
00:48:36,400 --> 00:48:38,639
About what, exactly, Todd?

736
00:48:38,640 --> 00:48:42,765
He's just been telling us about
his experiences, talking

737
00:48:45,080 --> 00:48:46,279
about them.

738
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:51,119
When he was in, uh, the
operation, Colton visited heaven.

739
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:52,439
But you said he didn't die.

740
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:56,565
He didn't, but he saw heaven.

741
00:48:56,880 --> 00:48:58,399
He saw Jesus and angels and...

742
00:48:58,400 --> 00:48:59,886
But how?

743
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:02,239
I don't know.

744
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:03,839
- Reverend Burpo.
- Todd.

745
00:49:03,840 --> 00:49:07,439
Todd. Some of the hospital staff
have said, off the record,

746
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:11,079
that your son was not expected to
survive and used the word "miracle."

747
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:12,319
How would you explain that?

748
00:49:12,320 --> 00:49:16,161
I haven't even
tried to, uh, do that.

749
00:49:16,280 --> 00:49:17,719
Can you try?

750
00:49:17,720 --> 00:49:20,239
If he didn't die, uh,
how could he see heaven?

751
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:22,199
I don't know, but he did.

752
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:24,368
Do you believe he was in heaven?

753
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:27,569
Uh...

754
00:49:29,080 --> 00:49:30,930
I know he saw something.

755
00:49:32,080 --> 00:49:34,089
It sure sounded like heaven.

756
00:49:35,240 --> 00:49:37,239
Good Lord, what's
happened to our preacher?

757
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:55,282
Well, I thought
that went well, huh?

758
00:49:58,280 --> 00:49:59,879
Nice view.

759
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:01,127
Mmm.

760
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:03,319
- I love being up so high.
- Mmm.

761
00:50:04,880 --> 00:50:08,079
Colton! Hey!

762
00:50:08,080 --> 00:50:11,011
I thought I asked you
to stop playing with that!

763
00:50:11,600 --> 00:50:13,279
I'm sorry, Dad!

764
00:50:13,280 --> 00:50:15,599
I told him not to, Dad!

765
00:50:15,600 --> 00:50:17,799
Half the church
wants to stop feeling

766
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:19,319
and start thinking.

767
00:50:19,320 --> 00:50:23,161
And the other half, they
want the exact opposite.

768
00:50:23,800 --> 00:50:25,525
This is Todd.

769
00:50:27,520 --> 00:50:28,767
Yeah.

770
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:35,490
Let me call you back.

771
00:50:37,280 --> 00:50:39,164
That was the newspaper.

772
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:43,009
They want to do
an article about heaven.

773
00:50:43,760 --> 00:50:45,007
And?

774
00:50:45,280 --> 00:50:47,562
And they want to interview Colton.

775
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:51,041
And you think that's a good idea?

776
00:50:52,120 --> 00:50:55,479
So, Colton, a lot of people
were praying for you.

777
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:56,999
I guess.

778
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,719
Well, that must feelgood.

779
00:50:58,720 --> 00:51:01,685
Come over here, buddy.
You're being interviewed.

780
00:51:02,440 --> 00:51:04,005
Thank you.

781
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:08,159
You were very sick.

782
00:51:08,160 --> 00:51:10,408
What did it feel like to die?

783
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:12,399
I didn't die.

784
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:14,250
But you went to heaven?

