01:09:05,080 --> 01:09:06,879
who died after the fire
in his motor home.

1043
01:09:06,880 --> 01:09:08,599
He didn't have any
friends or next of kin.

1044
01:09:08,600 --> 01:09:10,079
You've got Colton today.

1045
01:09:10,080 --> 01:09:11,439
I'm going to take him with me.

1046
01:09:11,440 --> 01:09:12,766
Great.

1047
01:09:15,440 --> 01:09:18,479
He's never been freaked out in those
situations. He's a lot of comfort.

1048
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:20,682
Oh, for the dead man or for you?

1049
01:09:21,640 --> 01:09:23,126
Touché.

1050
01:09:24,400 --> 01:09:26,125
Touché.Touché.

1051
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:35,999
Our Father who art in heaven,

1052
01:09:36,000 --> 01:09:37,799
hallowed be Thy name.

1053
01:09:37,800 --> 01:09:41,759
Thy kingdom come, Thy will be done

1054
01:09:41,760 --> 01:09:44,964
on earth as it is in heaven.

1055
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:47,442
Give us this day, our daily bread.

1056
01:09:49,920 --> 01:09:52,122
Aim. Begin.

1057
01:10:00,120 --> 01:10:02,159
You had a grandpa
named "Pop," right?

1058
01:10:02,160 --> 01:10:03,646
That's right.

1059
01:10:03,800 --> 01:10:07,004
Was he your daddy's daddy
or your mommy's daddy?

1060
01:10:07,200 --> 01:10:10,483
He was my mom's dad. He died
when I was about your age.

1061
01:10:11,720 --> 01:10:13,570
He's very nice.

1062
01:10:13,720 --> 01:10:16,924
You saw Pop?
You saw my grandfather?

1063
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:19,045
You saw him?

1064
01:10:19,960 --> 01:10:21,399
Where did you see him?

1065
01:10:21,400 --> 01:10:22,840
In heaven.

1066
01:10:25,160 --> 01:10:27,879
I loved my grandfather very much.

1067
01:10:27,880 --> 01:10:30,924
He was there with me
when my father couldn't be.

1068
01:10:31,200 --> 01:10:34,290
He taught me to weld.
He gave me that slingshot.

1069
01:10:34,480 --> 01:10:36,919
I know. We play with it.

1070
01:10:36,920 --> 01:10:39,521
That's right.
And he was a good man.

1071
01:10:39,800 --> 01:10:43,447
He was a really good man, but I
don't know what he believed in.

1072
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:45,444
None of us did.

1073
01:10:46,240 --> 01:10:47,726
I think

1074
01:10:48,200 --> 01:10:51,290
he's one of the reasons
your dad became a minister.

1075
01:10:52,680 --> 01:10:55,519
I was hoping he would get a
break getting into heaven then.

1076
01:10:55,520 --> 01:10:58,159
You don't have to worry, Dad.
He's there.

1077
01:10:58,160 --> 01:11:01,079
He came up to me and told
me he was your grandfather

1078
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:02,599
and you called him "Pop."

1079
01:11:02,600 --> 01:11:05,879
And he held me in his lap
just like Jesus did.

1080
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:09,050
And he told me
everything was all right.

1081
01:11:24,880 --> 01:11:27,447
Okay, look at this.

1082
01:11:28,520 --> 01:11:30,879
Is this him?
Is this the man you saw?

1083
01:11:30,880 --> 01:11:33,162
No. That's not who I saw.

1084
01:11:33,280 --> 01:11:36,079
Okay, but just look.
Are you sure? Colton?

1085
01:11:36,080 --> 01:11:39,559
Nobody wears glasses in heaven.

1086
01:11:39,560 --> 01:11:41,759
Can I go play? Because
when Mom gets home...

1087
01:11:41,760 --> 01:11:43,769
Are you sure that's not him?

1088
01:11:44,320 --> 01:11:45,879
- It's not him.
- Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

1089
01:11:45,880 --> 01:11:47,399
When Mom gets home...

1090
01:11:47,400 --> 01:11:48,719
Mom will be home in a second.

1091
01:11:48,720 --> 01:11:50,922
Just wait one second. Wait.

1092
01:12:33,840 --> 01:12:35,326
Colton?

1093
01:12:37,320 --> 01:12:40,364
That's him. That's Pop.

1094
01:12:41,440 --> 01:12:44,166
In heaven, everybody's young.

1095
01:12:46,760 --> 01:12:48,803
Are you okay, Dad?

1096
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:52,479
An awful lot happened
to you in heaven.

1097
01:12:52,480 --> 01:12:55,001
Yeah, it was amazing.

1098
01:13:12,480 --> 01:13:15,763
Todd, dinner is going
to be ready in five...

1099
01:13:19,160 --> 01:13:20,799
Are you okay?

1100
01:13:20,800 --> 01:13:22,604
Colton saw Pop.

1101
01:13:25,800 --> 01:13:28,128
In heaven. My grandfather.

1102
01:13:32,000 --> 01:13:34,159
I don't know what to make of this.

1103
01:13:34,160 --> 01:13:36,839
Well, I don't have the luxury
of not knowing, Sonja.

1104
01:13:36,840 --> 01:13:39,520
I don't. Everything he tells me,

1105
01:13:40,000 --> 01:13:43,761
it hits me, you know?
And I want to believe him.

1106
01:13:44,160 --> 01:13:46,919
Okay, I want to believe
him. He's four.

1107
01:13:46,920 --> 01:13:49,719
He's four. He's so innocent,
he can't be making this up,

1108
01:13:49,720 --> 01:13:52,366
but everything he talks
about is impossible.

1109
01:13:52,840 --> 01:13:56,519
It is a massive adventure
that he's created.

1110
01:13:56,520 --> 01:13:59,999
He's talking about Jesus,
seeing Jesus' horse.

1111
01:14:00,000 --> 01:14:03,044
He talks about choirs of
angels and my grandfather.

1112
01:14:03,440 --> 01:14:06,839
It would take weeks or days, but,
"For God a day is a thousand years."

1113
01:14:06,840 --> 01:14:08,679
"And a thousand years but a day."

1114
01:14:08,680 --> 01:14:10,119
I'm just saying that's scripture.

1115
01:14:10,120 --> 01:14:12,279
It's scripture. There's no clock.

1116
01:14:12,280 --> 01:14:14,719
There's no clock. Einstein
talks about the same thing.

1117
01:14:14,720 --> 01:14:16,439
"Some reality is beyond time."

1118
01:14:16,440 --> 01:14:18,722
Why can't it just be a mystery?

1119
01:14:18,880 --> 01:14:22,079
Because I think God might be trying
to reach out to us through Colton.

1120
01:14:22,080 --> 01:14:23,199
That's what I think.

1121
01:14:23,200 --> 01:14:27,199
What Colton is telling us, Todd,
is an echo of every story,

1122
01:14:27,200 --> 01:14:30,759
every song, every image he's
seen since he was a child.

1123
01:14:30,760 --> 01:14:33,850
Why does this have
to be a myth? Why?

1124
01:14:37,080 --> 01:14:41,439
I don't know. I don't
know how to move on

1125
01:14:41,440 --> 01:14:43,005
with my life.

1126
01:14:43,560 --> 01:14:45,524
Tell me what to do.

1127
01:14:53,400 --> 01:14:55,125
I don't know.

1128
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:02,799
All I care about is if my husband

1129
01:15:02,800 --> 01:15:05,844
and my family know
that I love them.

1130
01:15:09,840 --> 01:15:13,123
I'm sorry I can't help you
with any of this.

1131
01:16:02,640 --> 01:16:04,683
Well, I'm here.

1132
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:08,525
Where are you?

1133
01:17:13,040 --> 01:17:16,279
Please accept this flag as a
symbol of our appreciation

1134
01:17:16,280 --> 01:17:19,119
for your loved one's honorable
and faithful service.

1135
01:17:19,120 --> 01:17:22,767
Your son was a hero.
He died a brave marine.

1136
01:17:30,160 --> 01:17:31,521
You.

1137
01:17:35,080 --> 01:17:38,999
I always figured it was Jay leaving

1138
01:17:39,000 --> 01:17:42,283
flags and flowers
here on my son's grave.

1139
01:17:46,320 --> 01:17:48,363
I failed you, Nancy.

1140
01:17:50,600 --> 01:17:53,519
The worst moment of your life,

1141
01:17:53,520 --> 01:17:57,725
loss beyond comprehension,
and I had...

1142
01:17:59,600 --> 01:18:01,370
I had nothing for you.

1143
01:18:01,640 --> 01:18:03,490
No comfort.

1144
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:06,406
No hope.

1145
01:18:07,840 --> 01:18:09,405
No peace.

1146
01:18:10,200 --> 01:18:11,479
I should have maybe...

1147
01:18:11,480 --> 01:18:13,279
No, you didn't let me down.

1148
01:18:13,280 --> 01:18:16,643
You couldn't take my pain away
and I didn't want it gone.

1149
01:18:16,840 --> 01:18:19,361
For a while, pain was all
I had of him.

1150
01:18:26,800 --> 01:18:29,526
You don't have to
save the world, Todd.

1151
01:18:31,120 --> 01:18:33,846
I believe that's already been done.

1152
01:18:38,040 --> 01:18:40,322
Since that meeting at the church

1153
01:18:41,400 --> 01:18:45,924
where I was the bitter woman
I swore I'd never be,

1154
01:18:47,640 --> 01:18:49,410
I've been thinking.

1155
01:18:54,200 --> 01:18:57,210
It's not the people of
the church I'm mad at.

1156
01:18:58,920 --> 01:19:02,522
And it's not you. Not your son.

1157
01:19:06,240 --> 01:19:07,885
It's God.

1158
01:19:09,680 --> 01:19:14,363
Why God would give you your
son back and take mine away.

1159
01:19:17,520 --> 01:19:19,882
When Colton was in that hospital,

1160
01:19:21,400 --> 01:19:23,364
I saw he was dying

1161
01:19:25,600 --> 01:19:27,802
and some part of me broke.

1162
01:19:30,000 --> 01:19:32,646
Some part that still hasn't mended.

1163
01:19:34,120 --> 01:19:38,239
Nancy, you don't ever
have to apologize to me

1164
01:19:38,240 --> 01:19:40,761
for any broken part you carry.

1165
01:19:52,200 --> 01:19:54,004
Do you think...

1166
01:19:55,280 --> 01:19:57,130
I have to ask.

1167
01:20:01,120 --> 01:20:03,971
Do you think my son went to heaven?

1168
01:20:07,400 --> 01:20:11,241
Do you love your son still?

1169
01:20:11,440 --> 01:20:13,085
Of course.

1170
01:20:14,240 --> 01:20:16,079
Do you think I love mine?

1171
01:20:16,080 --> 01:20:17,805
I know you do.

1172
01:20:19,320 --> 01:20:22,967
Do you think I love my son
more than you love yours?

1173
01:20:27,400 --> 01:20:28,840
No.

1174
01:20:29,560 --> 01:20:34,687
Do you think God loves my son
more than he loves yours?

1175
01:21:06,440 --> 01:21:08,119
Mommy?

1176
01:21:08,120 --> 01:21:09,799
Yes, Colton.

1177
01:21:09,800 --> 01:21:11,843
Did you know I have a sister?

1178
01:21:12,480 --> 01:21:15,490
Yes, Colton, of course,
I know you have a sister.

1179
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:17,525
I didn't know.

1180
01:21:18,440 --> 01:21:21,166
You didn't know that
Cassie is your sister?

1181
01:21:21,280 --> 01:21:23,881
No, I have two sisters.

1182
01:21:28,040 --> 01:21:31,323
You had a baby die in
your tummy, didn't you?

1183
01:21:41,640 --> 01:21:44,571
Honey, who told you I had
a baby die in my tummy?

1184
01:21:44,680 --> 01:21:47,770
She told me she died in your tummy.

1185
01:21:56,880 --> 01:21:58,809
What does she look like?

1186
01:21:59,680 --> 01:22:02,565
Like Cassie, but a little smaller.

1187
01:22:02,600 --> 01:22:04,839
And hair like yours.

1188
01:22:04,840 --> 01:22:07,839
In heaven, this little
girl came up to me

1189
01:22:07,840 --> 01:22:10,088
and she wouldn't stop hugging me.

1190
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:21,079
Honey, what did...
What was her name?

1191
01:22:21,080 --> 01:22:24,727
She didn't have a name.
You guys didn't name her.

1192
01:22:32,760 --> 01:22:35,327
You're right. We didn't. We, uh...

1193
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:39,846
We didn't know
that she was a "she."

1194
01:22:44,280 --> 01:22:46,767
- Are you okay, Mommy?
- Yeah.

1195
01:22:50,040 --> 01:22:52,402
We lost a baby, sweetheart,

1196
01:22:52,880 --> 01:22:55,242
just a few months before she was...

1197
01:22:56,800 --> 01:22:58,081
Todd.

1198
01:23:01,480 --> 01:23:04,286
That's our baby.
That's our little girl.

1199
01:23:07,240 --> 01:23:08,919
She's okay.

1200
01:23:13,240 --> 01:23:17,279
I don't want to be late for school
today and the phone's ringing!

1201
01:23:17,280 --> 01:23:18,891
I'll get it.

1202
01:23:23,800 --> 01:23:25,079
Hi.

1203
01:23:25,080 --> 01:23:26,159
Pastor Todd Burpo?

1204
01:23:26,160 --> 01:23:27,319
This is Todd.

1205
01:23:27,320 --> 01:23:29,319
Great. We're live on
the air with Todd Burpo.

1206
01:23:29,320 --> 01:23:31,599
Can you tell us about your
son's adventure in heaven?

1207
01:23:31,600 --> 01:23:33,239
- On the air?
- Dad!

1208
01:23:33,240 --> 01:23:35,679
Everybody here in Imperial followed
the story of your son's sickness

1209
01:23:35,680 --> 01:23:38,079
and people all over town were
praying for his recovery.

1210
01:23:38,080 --> 01:23:40,919
Now we're starting to hear of an
amazing trip he took to heaven.

1211
01:23:40,920 --> 01:23:43,199
Can you tell us about that?

1212
01:23:43,200 --> 01:23:46,131
Come by Crossroads
Wesleyan Church on Sunday.

1213
01:23:48,120 --> 01:23:50,322
I'll tell you all about it.

1214
01:23:57,600 --> 01:24:01,088
♪ Here's my heart now

1215
01:24:01,200 --> 01:24:03,639
♪ Take and seal it

1216
01:24:03,640 --> 01:24:09,244
♪ Seal it for Thy courts above

1217
01:24:09,640 --> 01:24:13,242
♪ Here's my heart now

1218
01:24:13,480 --> 01:24:16,923
♪ Take and seal it

1219
01:24:17,040 --> 01:24:21,245
♪ Seal it for Thy courts

1220
01:24:22,800 --> 01:24:26,368
♪ Above ♪

1221
01:24:28,800 --> 01:24:30,570
I love you.

1222
01:24:47,160 --> 01:24:50,921
I'm standing here today with
wounds that are still healing,

1223
01:24:51,760 --> 01:24:54,159
fears that are still echoing

1224
01:24:54,160 --> 01:24:55,519
and in that way, maybe some of you

1225
01:24:55,520 --> 01:24:57,999
are sitting here this
morning exactly like me.

1226
01:24:58,000 --> 01:25:01,839
I can say truthfully that
the pain that I suffered,

1227
01:25:01,840 --> 01:25:07,809
it was nothing compared to watching
my son that close to death.

1228
01:25:09,200 --> 01:25:13,041
So, now we've got a question.

1229
01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:16,129
Was Colton in heaven?

1230
01:25:21,080 --> 01:25:22,406
Yes.

1231
01:25:22,880 --> 01:25:25,481
He was in the heaven
that God showed him.

1232
01:25:27,600 --> 01:25:29,404
Is heaven real?

1233
01:25:29,560 --> 01:25:31,967
'Cause, if heaven is for real,

1234
01:25:32,280 --> 01:25:35,689
we'd all lead different
lives, wouldn't we?

1235
01:25:37,800 --> 01:25:39,331
Would we?

1236
01:25:41,120 --> 01:25:44,079
Really? Haven't we
already seen heaven?

1237
01:25:44,080 --> 01:25:49,127
In the first cry of a baby,
the courage of a friend,

1238
01:25:49,600 --> 01:25:51,439
the hands of a nurse

1239
01:25:51,440 --> 01:25:53,759
or a doctor, the love
of a mother or father.

1240
01:25:53,760 --> 01:25:56,279
Haven't we already
had a glimpse of heaven

1241
01:25:56,280 --> 01:26:00,371
and so often chosen the hell

1242
01:26:01,320 --> 01:26:04,444
of hate and fear?

1243
01:26:05,680 --> 01:26:06,919
Is heaven for real?

1244
01:26:06,920 --> 01:26:09,239
Every single one of you
has asked that question.

1245
01:26:09,240 --> 01:26:12,364
All of us have. And
for me, the answer...

1246
01:26:14,800 --> 01:26:16,445
It's "yes."

1247
01:26:16,920 --> 01:26:20,169
I see it, so I believe it.

1248
01:26:20,760 --> 01:26:23,679
And what we believe
changes what we perceive.

1249
01:26:23,680 --> 01:26:28,488
And I believe that God, he's love.

1250
01:26:30,760 --> 01:26:33,759
Ten thousand times I've been
here and I've talked about

1251
01:26:33,760 --> 01:26:35,849
"On earth as it is in heaven."

1252
01:26:36,320 --> 01:26:39,330
And I don't know that
I ever listened to that.

1253
01:26:42,440 --> 01:26:47,119
And my son, he saw something.
He saw heaven.

1254
01:26:47,120 --> 01:26:49,368
He'll tell you all about Jesus.

1255
01:26:49,960 --> 01:26:52,242
How about that name? "Jesus."

1256
01:26:54,120 --> 01:26:55,890
Ooh.

1257
01:26:55,960 --> 01:26:57,491
"Jesus."

1258
01:26:59,640 --> 01:27:02,411
It creates so much hope
in so many of you,

1259
01:27:03,320 --> 01:27:05,841
so much distrust in so many others.

1260
01:27:07,040 --> 01:27:08,730
That's okay.

1261
01:27:09,200 --> 01:27:12,159
I believe God asked me
to be a pastor.

1262
01:27:12,160 --> 01:27:15,039
Did he insist on my vision
being the same as yours?

1263
01:27:15,040 --> 01:27:16,685
Or yours?

1264
01:27:18,240 --> 01:27:22,199
Of course not. Did he make
me one of those heroes like

1265
01:27:22,200 --> 01:27:25,839
that lion and the bear and
unicorn I preached about?

1266
01:27:25,840 --> 01:27:30,045
No. That's what I wanted.
God had a different plan.

1267
01:27:33,040 --> 01:27:36,767
God crushed my pride.

1268
01:27:40,320 --> 01:27:42,284
He opened my heart

1269
01:27:52,000 --> 01:27:53,770
to love.

1270
01:27:59,200 --> 01:28:01,448
And all I have to do,

1271
01:28:03,560 --> 01:28:05,762
the one thing this love requires

1272
01:28:07,760 --> 01:28:10,645
is that I let others know
they're not alone.

1273
01:28:39,000 --> 01:28:41,168
So amazing.

1274
01:28:43,720 --> 01:28:46,321
Welcome back. Good work, buddy.

1275
01:28:48,080 --> 01:28:50,159
It's good to see you.

1276
01:28:50,160 --> 01:28:51,600
Hey, Randy.

1277
01:28:54,640 --> 01:28:57,286
Are things okay over there?

1278
01:29:24,760 --> 01:29:26,759
What? What? What was that?

1279
01:29:26,760 --> 01:29:29,486
- Hey, thanks very much, John.
- You're welcome.

1280
01:29:29,600 --> 01:29:32,087
Thanks. You, too. I am.

1281
01:29:36,800 --> 01:29:38,490
Hey, Ray.

1282
01:29:52,240 --> 01:29:56,001
She picked up the brush when
she was just six years old.

1283
01:29:56,640 --> 01:29:58,319
But the visions...

1284
01:29:58,320 --> 01:30:00,359
- Mom, can I have some lemonade, please?
- Of course.

1285
01:30:00,360 --> 01:30:02,679
- Started when she was just four.
- Uh-huh.

1286
01:30:02,680 --> 01:30:04,319
Look at this on CNN.

1287
01:30:04,320 --> 01:30:05,559
She's a self-taught painter.

1288
01:30:05,560 --> 01:30:07,639
It's about a girl on the
other side of the world

1289
01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:10,286
who had an experience
a lot like Colton's.

1290
01:30:10,480 --> 01:30:14,082
She saw visions of heaven.
Look at this. Angels.

1291
01:30:14,520 --> 01:30:17,359
She began to describe to her
mother in great detail...

1292
01:30:17,360 --> 01:30:18,839
Look at this, honey.
